title: Al-Qaeda leader taunts Trump after botched Navy SEAL raid | Daily Mail Online
text: Botched Navy SEAL raid was secretly targeting leader of Al-Qaeda in the Arabian Peninsula who is now taunting Donald Trump as the 'fool of the White House' Last week's Navy SEAL raid on Yemen was ordered to target al-Qaeda chief Al-Qaeda's head operative in the Arabian Peninsula - Qassim al-Rimi - was supposed to be killed or captured Al-Rimi is still alive and appeared to taunt Donald Trump in audio recording Terrorist considered world's 3rd most dangerous said scores of US soldiers were killed or wounded during raid The raid also left an eight-year-old American girl dead and a member of SEAL Team 6 Published: 04:22 GMT, 7 February 2017 | Updated: 09:45 GMT, 7 February 2017 424 shares
